Hello Claude271. To start, I don't take LSD.
It happens to me to take speed or downers but not LSD, ketamine or anything else.
I think you should just see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you still smell like that kind of "side effect" it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you should go see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you a treatment or emergency medication.
Otherwise there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good luck. Peace
Hello Claude271,
Having passed through the state you describe (following a mix of gossips, micropointes, taz, keta, in short, everything that passed through there),
If I can give you advice, it's just to tell you that it's all just psychological.
The more you take it to heart, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe softly, and you curl up in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you may feel like they're closing in on you).
After several months of use, especially when mixing, you can still experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of these voices that clutter your head.
Keep fishing, and stay positive.
